# Auto-Imports in Vue Files

This project uses two unplugin packages (configured in `vite.config.ts`) that make symbols and components globally available **without** explicit imports. Do NOT add import statements for any of them.

## 1. Auto-imported functions & composables (`unplugin-auto-import`)

### Vue core

`ref`, `computed`, `reactive`, `readonly`, `watch`, `watchEffect`, `watchPostEffect`, `watchSyncEffect`, `toRef`, `toRefs`, `toRaw`, `toValue`, `unref`, `isRef`, `isReactive`, `isReadonly`, `isProxy`, `isShallow`, `shallowRef`, `shallowReactive`, `shallowReadonly`, `triggerRef`, `customRef`, `markRaw`, `nextTick`, `provide`, `inject`, `h`, `defineComponent`, `defineAsyncComponent`, `resolveComponent`, `createApp`, `effectScope`, `EffectScope`, `getCurrentInstance`, `getCurrentScope`, `getCurrentWatcher`, `onScopeDispose`, `onWatcherCleanup`, `useAttrs`, `useSlots`, `useCssModule`, `useCssVars`, `useId`, `useModel`, `useTemplateRef`, `onMounted`, `onBeforeMount`, `onUnmounted`, `onBeforeUnmount`, `onUpdated`, `onBeforeUpdate`, `onActivated`, `onDeactivated`, `onErrorCaptured`, `onRenderTracked`, `onRenderTriggered`, `onServerPrefetch`

### Inertia.js

`router`, `useForm`, `usePage`

### vue-i18n

`useI18n`

### momentum-trail-patch

`route`, `current`

### momentum-lock

`can`

### Project composables (from `resources/js/composables/`)

`useAppearance`, `initializeTheme`, `updateTheme`, `useCurrentUrl`, `useInitials`, `getInitials`, `useTwoFactorAuth`

### Authoritative list

`resources/js/types/auto-imports.d.ts` — if a symbol is missing from that file, it still requires an explicit import.

## 2. Auto-imported components (`unplugin-vue-components`)

All `.vue` files inside `resources/js/components/` (including subdirectories) are registered as global components. Use them directly in `<template>` without importing. This includes all UI primitives (`Button`, `Input`, `Card`, `Select`, `Modal`, `Sheet`, `Sidebar`, etc.), app-specific components (`PropertyCard`, `PropertyFilters`, `Heading`, `Breadcrumbs`, `PaginationNav`, etc.), and Inertia's `<Link>` and `<Head>`.

Icons using the `icon-` prefix (e.g. `<icon-custom-logo />`) are also auto-resolved via `unplugin-icons`.

### Authoritative list

`resources/js/types/components.d.ts` — if a component is missing from that file, it still requires an explicit import.

## What still needs explicit imports

Types, interfaces, utilities, Wayfinder actions/routes (`@/actions/...`, `@/routes/...`), third-party libraries not listed above, and any symbol not present in the two `.d.ts` files above.
